Interpret the Pattern:

Lower numbers of heads (e.g., 2â€“4) are more likely under the fair coin (0.5).

Higher numbers of heads (e.g., 7â€“10) are more likely under the biased coin (0.7).

Example:
Suppose we observe 3 heads out of 10 tosses:

ğ‘ƒ(3 headsâˆ£0.5)=0.117
