0.117/0.009=13

â‡’ The result (3 heads) is 13 times more likely if the coin were fair than if it were biased.

Key Concept â€” Likelihood Ratio:

The likelihood ratio quantifies how much more likely one hypothesis is compared to the other, given the observed data.

Likelihood Ratio=ğ‘ƒ(dataâˆ£ğ»0)ğ‘ƒ(dataâˆ£ğ»1)
