A higher ratio supports the null hypothesis (Hâ‚€); a lower ratio supports the alternative hypothesis (Hâ‚).

Takeaway:

This simple coin example illustrates the core logic of hypothesis testing:

We compare how probable our observed data is under two competing hypotheses.

The more likely explanation (based on computed probabilities) guides our decision.

This reasoning forms the basis for all hypothesis tests â€” whether about coins, customer arrivals, or machine performance.
